    // right_one_dist[n-1] is 0 if a[n-1]=1, or n+1 if a[n-1]=0.
    // This means for i=0, min(left_one_dist[0], right_one_dist[0]) will be 0 if a[0]=1,
    // or right_one_dist[0] if a[0]=0 and there's a 1 to its right.
    // But the rule for b_1 and b_n overrides this.
    // So, we must ensure final_a[0] = a[0] and final_a[n-1] = a[n-1].
