            // The final coordinates (n,m) must have the same parity as the number of moves k,
            // if we consider the Manhattan distance.
            // (n+m) % 2 must be equal to k % 2.
            // If (n+m) % 2 != k % 2, it's impossible.
            // This is equivalent to (k - (n+m)) % 2 != 0.
