        // In this case, we can use `(k-m)/2` pairs of (1,1) and (-1,-1) moves.
        // Each such pair adds 2 diagonal moves. So, `k-m` diagonal moves are added.
        // Total diagonal moves: `n + (k-m)`.

        // If `k` and `m` have different parities, then `k-m` is odd.
        // We cannot use only pairs of (1,1) and (-1,-1) to use up an odd number of moves.
        // We must use at least one axial move to change the parity of the total path length.
