        // `(n+m - k) mod 2` vs `(n+k-m) mod 2`.
        // `(n+m - k) - (n+k-m) = 2m - 2k = 2(m-k)`, which is even.
        // So, `(n+m-k)` and `(n+k-m)` always have the same parity.
        // This means this formula `n + k - m` is consistent with the parity constraint.

        // If `(k-m)` is odd:
        // We cannot simply add `k-m` diagonal moves.
        // We need to make an adjustment.
        // We need to change the parity of the number of diagonal moves.
